<br>
I loved the movie and have my own theories about what the Matrix is all about. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pecc>Pecc</A> at: 5/16/03 12:21:34 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=annihilusmaximus>Annihilus Maximus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:yellow;'>Tavern Ale Swiller</span></span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(5/16/03 1:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3256.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Matrix: Reloaded</span><hr size=1> Movie was great once you got passed the overly drawn out sex/dance section there. That whole 20-30 minutes in Xion was boring imo.<br>
<br>
The religous references scattered throughout were interesting and made me theorize a few thigns abotu their plans. Many of the characters fall into various roles from the Bible. Agent Smith with his desire to eradicate all of humanity is The Beast. The Oracle and The Architect are God and Lucifer, but in a reversed role where Lucifer created Earth (The Matrix) and God created Hell (Xion) after he fell from grace (became an exiled program). Neo is of course Jesus, actually on his 6th resurection it seems. Morpheus is the snake in the garden of eden, offering pills instead of fruit. <br>
<br>
Oh and there is the guardian of the Oracle. Sitting legs crossed as Neo enters the room, when Neo scans the code you see that he is all gold.... almost looks like a Bhudda statue.<br>
<br>
I'm sure there is more but those were the ones obvious to me on first viewing.<br>
<br>
What I'm wondering now is how they explain Neo's powers in the real world in the next flick. It didnt seem to be the same as his Matrix powers, but more like he still has a connection to all the machines.<br>
<br>
Overall I was impressed with it, will watch it again in the theaters, and eagerly await the 3rd movie. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stalpus>Stalpus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 894<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(5/16/03 6:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3256.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> It's all about mind over matter, telekenisis.  Seeing zion was interesting, but I agree that the sex/dance thing went on a little too long.  Was it just me or was Morpheus' speach seem a little too forced?<br>
