<br>
SPOILERS FOLLOW<br>
*<br>
*<br>
*<br>
*<br>
*<br>
*<br>
*<br>
*<br>
*<br>
*<br>
*<br>
*<br>
*<br>
*<br>
*<br>
<br>
Morpheus isn't wrong or crazy, just badly misinformed. He is totally unaware that this whole &quot;war&quot; has already occured six times before, and he IS right about one thing. The One reaching the Source DOES bring about the end of the war, because each of the previous six times The One has chosen the &quot;safe&quot; path and reloaded the Matrix thus (technically) ending the war. Zion is then destroyed and rebuilt so the Anomaly can be contained for another cycle.<br>
<br>
This time though, Neo choses a different path and the Architect (be he machine, program or even a real person) can no longer predict what is going to occur. The Architect made a point of the fact that Neo was reacting &quot;differently&quot; this time around and was obviously pained when he chose the other door.<br>
<br>
Agent Smith is going to be the undoing of the Matrix. In freeing him from the system and thereby robbing him of his of purpose (by &quot;killing&quot; him in the first movie) Neo has created a program that is simply malicious and much like a cancer (or virus) will reproduce itself until the entire system is under it's control or simply grinds to halt, either of which is just fine with Smith. He's going to be the real problem in the 3rd movie.<br>
<br>
Zion is quite likely just another extension of the Matrix. A real one, however. After each One reloads the Matrix, he remains outside with 23 people to restart Zion which is rebuilt by the machines to give the next Anamoly time and reason to proceed in the same manner as all the Ones before. Zion is basically the &quot;control group&quot; for the experiment that is the Matrix. One the Anomaly has presented itself and the Matrix has been reloaded, the control group is cleared to provide a clean slate for the next reboot and ensure that any memory of the reboot would be held at best as myth and fable, not fact.<br>
<br>
Merovignian is either a Vampire, a previous One or just a plain renegade program from a previous boot of the Matrix. Same with the two Werewolves (one of which Persephone shot in the face) and the twins (who are ghosts). I don't know what role he will play in the 3rd movie, but I suspect Persephone is more important. Refer to the mythology regarding Persephone, when she is captive the world is cold and dark. When she is free the world is light and warm. And then there's the kiss she demanded. I don't fully understand the importance of that.<br>
<br>
Cog<br>
<br>
