<br>
When Neo met the Architect, listening to the explanations alone was quite interesting, and one of the things that came to mind was, how do we know what the architect is saying is true, it could be another form of control or attempted control over Neo who has the ability to help bring down the matrix. Would you tell him he has that capability or would you try to lead him to believe either way he chooses will bring the end of humanity, although one way might allow it to re-establish itself for the machines use.<br>
<br>
There are a lot of nuances and background things going on that you can miss easily if you dont listen to some of the statements. I found it to be not quite as good as the first story wise, SFX wise it was easily superior.<br>
<br>
Matrix: Revolutions looks good and at least its only 6 months away.<br>
