Morpheus being the serpent, never realized that.  Suppose it makes sense, removed the blissful shroud to reveal what's real.<br>
<br>
Thoughts on the Neo being able to control shit outside of the Matrix....  I think that may be why the Architect always tried to reload the matrix and end the cycle of the one.  Perhaps if he chose the right door, he would become more powerful or have access to more control, sorta like upgrading or unlocking more potential he was aware of.  There's no reason the Architect would be forced to tell the truth though.  Also, I wonder if he has a connection with it outside of it to the point of where he went into the coma in the real world, he was still logged in the Matrix?  Sorta like .hack//SIGN.  Honestly, between the two of these, I'm loving the whole inside a computer storyline.  Just really works / clicks with me.<br>
<br>
And aye, I stayed through for the preview of Revolutions.  Looks like Neo is gonna have to beat the shit outta a few hundred more Smith's.  =)  On the topic, anyone flat out love when Neo was using the pipe on all the Smiths?  Fucking knocked them around like rag dolls, had me laughing so hard at some points.  Special effects in this movie were below the previous I thought, but don't get me wrong, it SOOOO didn't take away from the movie.  Loved it, can't wait to see those big ass armor things in Zion blowing shit up.  Ahhh.... War.... so wonderful when it's on a screen and not real.<br>
