<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I watched the movie last night and gave it an 8 out of 10 stars.  My favorite fight scene definitely had to be in the foyer of the mansion with all the different weapons and the jumping back and forth.  Least impressive was the cgi for the Agent Smith royal rumble.  On with the theories...<br>
<br>
As far as Neo being able to control outside forces (i.e. stopping the Sentinels after their hoover ship gets destroyed), I believe the reason he was able to do this is because he is in the &quot;second&quot; layer of the matrix (a la &quot;The Thirteenth Floor&quot;).  Essentially he is in a matrix inside a matrix.  All this time Neo thought he knew what the difference was between the real world and the matrix, but come to find out the &quot;real&quot; world is actually matrix 2.0.  This explains his powers here and why Agent Smith was able to corrupt that other Zion soldier.<br>
<br>
Any one catch the song title of the group Jueno (sp?).  Their song name was &quot;Mona Lisa Overdrive&quot;.  Very fitting since this was a title of a short story written by William Gibson (author of &quot;Neuromancer&quot;, 1983 and coiner of the word &quot;matrix&quot;).  Another movie was made based on this short story, &quot;Johnny Mnemonic&quot; starring Keanu Reeves.  I smell conspiracy...  As an aside, if you love the cyberpunk / &quot;matrix-esque&quot; type of movies, I seriously suggest you read &quot;Neuromancer&quot;.  Extremely good read.  Cyberpunk classic.<br>
<br>
